    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 1: </strong>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chicken </strong>and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until lightly browned</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 casserole dishes!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into chunks</p><p>Once lightly browned, reduce to a medium-high heat and add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and your<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>, then give it a good mix up and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> with 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil, then put the dish in the oven and cook, covered, for 25-30 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stew</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, reboil a little water in a kettle and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into chunks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a large splash of <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the potatoes to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray, then put the tray in the oven for 35-40 min or until the potatoes are tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew has had 25 min, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your <strong>soft cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stew</strong></p><p>Transfer<strong> half </strong>the<strong> creamy stew</strong> to a container and cool quickly (within 2 hours max) and refrigerate in a covered container. Enjoy within 24 hours</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped peppers </strong>to the dish with your <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for a final 10-12 min or until the sauce is thickened<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>marry me chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is ready, remove the potatoes from the oven, then discard the tin foil and crush the<strong> cooked potatoes </strong>firmly with a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>marry me chicken</strong> with the <strong>crushed potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meal 2:</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle, then wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta and reserve a little starchy pasta water</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>creamy stew</strong> to a pot with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook over a high heat, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go, for 6-7 min or until it is piping hot throughout</p><p>You can only reheat your food once, then enjoy straight away</p><p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your<strong> basil </strong>finely, including the stalks and keep the <strong>remaining basil leaves</strong> whole</p><p>Once it is piping hot, stir through your <strong>spinach</strong>,<strong> chopped basil</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save some for a garnish!) and the <strong>drained pasta </strong>with a splash of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>,<strong> </strong>then cook for a further 1-2 min \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy chicken & basil pasta</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/2-meals-marry-me-chicken-stew-and-creamy-chicken-and-basil-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season the <strong>creamy chicken & basil pasta </strong>with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>creamy chicken & basil pasta</strong> and top with the <strong>remaining grated Italian cheese </strong>and the <strong>whole basil leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
